properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 8 at 2:13PM CST until January 9 at 2:00PM CST by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
properties.description:
...MIXED PRECIPITATION DEVELOPING THURSDAY...

.A Winter Weather Advisory has been issued for Rusk County in west
central Wisconsin for a combination of freezing drizzle and light
snow on Thursday.

A storm system will develop later tonight and move from the
central plains, northeast across the Upper Midwest by Thursday
afternoon. Light precipitation in the form of snow, and freezing
drizzle will develop Thursday morning, and continue through the
early afternoon before temperatures rise above freezing. A quick
one inch of snow and a light glaze of ice is likely in Rusk
County. The will cause area roads to become hazardous.

* WHAT...Mixed precipitation expected. Total snow accumulations of
up to one inch and ice accumulations of a light glaze, or
possibly up to a ten of an inch.

* WHERE...Rusk County.

* WHEN...From 8 AM to 2 PM CST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 8 AM TO 2 PM CST THURSDAY
